Here is a basic template that can be used as a starting point for calculating the offset of an elements in an array:
```c
int getElementOffset(array, size, index) {
    return (index * size) + array;
}
```
This function takes three parameters: `array`, which is the pointer to the first element of the array, `size`, which is the number of elements in the array, and `index`, which is the zero-based index of the element for which you want to calculate the offset. The function returns the offset of the specified element in the array.

Note that this is just a basic template, and you may need to modify it depending on your specific needs. For example, if your array is two-dimensional, you would need to pass in the dimensions of the array as well as the index of the element.

